&nbsp;
&nbsp; In the video you see the man talking, while under the scrolls a text in Arabic and Hebrew that reads: "Time is about to expire. Your government is lying." The video, published on the Telegram channel of the group, is third filmed in less than a month of prisoners held in Gaza. On April 27, the group released a clip showing two live hostages: Keith Siegel and Omri Miran. Three days before another video was broadcast showing Hersh Goldberg-Polin. According to Israeli officials, 128 hostages held in Palestinian territory, including 36 deaths.
&nbsp;
Nadav Popplewell, in the video, has a black eye but not other visible wounds, tells the Jerusalem Post. The man, who also has the British nationality, had been seized on October 7 in the attack of Hamas in which he was killed his brother. Popplewell is diabetic and her sister, in an interview with Daily Mail in November, said she was worried about her health conditions during the prison. Popplewell's mother had been released on 24 November following the temporary ceasefire and hostage release agreement.&nbsp;
